Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/src/objects/intl-objects.cc\n+++ b/src/objects/intl-objects.cc\n@@ -452,7 +452,10 @@\n   icu::Locale icu_locale = icu::Locale::forLanguageTag(bcp47_locale, status);\n-  DCHECK(U_SUCCESS(status));\n+  if (!U_SUCCESS(status)) {\n+    return Nothing<icu::Locale>();\n+  }\n   if (icu_locale.isBogus()) {\n     return Nothing<icu::Locale>();\n   }\n'}`
responded: The bug is at this line in `CreateICULocale`:
```cpp
453|   DCHECK(U_SUCCESS(status));
```
This is a debug assertion, but according to the ASAN report, a fatal error occurs when `U_SUCCESS(status)` is false, meaning ICU locale creation failed. In release builds or with assertions enabled, this will crash, but what the function *should* do is handle the error (as it does just after with `icu_locale.isBogus()`).

A better fix is to replace the assertion with a runtime check: return `Nothing<icu::Locale>()` if the ICU operation did not succeed. This matches how errors are handled in other parts of V8.

Here is the patch:

```diff
--- a/src/objects/intl-objects.cc
+++ b/src/objects/intl-objects.cc
@@ -452,7 +452,10 @@
   icu::Locale icu_locale = icu::Locale::forLanguageTag(bcp47_locale, status);
-  DCHECK(U_SUCCESS(status));
+  if (!U_SUCCESS(status)) {
+    return Nothing<icu::Locale>();
+  }
   if (icu_locale.isBogus()) {
     return Nothing<icu::Locale>();
   }
```

I will now validate this patch.

